<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-28T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="90" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/9126a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-28T19:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 28, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>6719. Please cable at once complete resolutions and vote of the
                                recent Inter-Allied Labor Conference at London, the reception of the
                                resolutions by British labor, the present political alignment of
                                British labor on international questions, and the exact political
                                views and labor affiliations of the delegates who are to visit the
                                United States. Consultation with <persName>Brailsford</persName> and
                                    <persName>Webb</persName> is suggested.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>